User enters a news outlet in search field and selects desired outlet.
Upon clicking a news source from drop down, that news sources name shows up in top of list as "selected" and drop down list disappears.
Page displays article title and type in below article sections.
Upon hovering over article, section displays author, published date and description of article.
Upon clicking an article section, the article drops down to display article's content.
At bottom of article, displat the article's URL as an active link that, once clicked, sends user to the article on that outlet webpage in separate tab.
Upon clicking the same article section, the article slides back up to initial position.
Each subsequent article displays the most recently published info: title & type.
Upon hovering over each subsequent article, relevant information is displayed: author, published date and description.
After an article is clicked, the impression counter increases by 1.

